    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on March 30 about France's debate over national identity and its role in the presidential election misstated a provision of a law that regulates the wearing of head scarves by Muslim girls and women, one of the cultural issues with which the nation has struggled. The 2004 law bans head scarves in French primary and secondary schools; it does not apply to higher education.</p>
      </block>
